On January 15, 2019, President Trump welcomed the Clemson University Tigers football team to the White House to celebrate their victory in the 2018 College Football National Championship. The President praised the team's accomplishments and recognized their undefeated 15-0 record, stating that they were the first team to achieve this since 1897. He also commended the team's academic achievements, with 26 players earning their degrees. Coach Dabo Swinney and University President Jim Clements also spoke, expressing their gratitude for the recognition and highlighting the team's commitment to excellence both on and off the field. The event concluded with a visit to the Oval Office for photos.